feat(income): tap income on Home opens a drill-down of ONLY income deposits

Hemanth: tapping "other inflows" must NOT dump me into all transactions - it
should show only the deposits that make up the income number, and let me edit
them there. Slice 1 of the income-customization work (cap/split is next).

- New ManageIncomeSheet: a keyboard-safe bottom sheet listing exactly the
  month's income deposits (flow-intent income: salary / gift_in / interest /
  cash_in), with the total + per-deposit type. Each row edits in place: rename,
  "Not income" (flow_intent -> transfer_self), or Exclude.
- New pure selector incomeRowsForMonth() reconciles to the BudgetBox income
  number (same inference path), structure-based not amount-based (lists ALL
  income inflows, not the size-derived "biggest = paycheck" subset).
- The BudgetBox "of $X income" line is now tappable (and the existing
  "other inflows" chip) -> opens the sheet instead of /transactions.
- The "other inflows" chip now derives from the SAME flow-intent income rows,
  so marking a deposit "not income"/excluded updates it live (was raw inflows).

Bug found via live testing + fixed (P0): pruneAnnotation silently DROPPED
flow_intent, so the override reverted on save - this also silently broke the
transactions row-editor's intent flip. Now preserved; regression test added.

Verified live on 390px: 2 deposits -> drill-down shows both -> "Not income" on
the gift drops income $6,500 -> $5,000 live. pnpm verify green; +7 tests.

